sessions.title: Pokemon Trading Card Game - Open Gaming
Furry Psychology with Dr. Nuka and Furscience!
sessions.description: Want to know what makes furries tick? Let Dr. Nuka and the Furscience team take you through more than a decade of research on the furry fandom. Whether you're a veteran greymuzzle or new to the fandom, you're sure to learn something about this weird and wonderful fandom of ours!

sessions.title: Meet The Charity
sessions.description: TBD

sessions.title: Culinary Furry Meet and Greet
sessions.description:
Are you a furry who has a passion for the culinary arts? Do you have a recipe you've been dying to share? Now is your chance!

We're inviting cooks and bakers of all skill levels to bring copies of their favourite recipes to trade and share with others. Join in on casual discussions about your love for food while collecting recipes to add to your cookbook!

sessions.title: Your First Furry Convention
sessions.description: Welcome to your first furry convention! If you're new and would like to know what exactly is going on and how to make the most of it, this is the panel for you! We'll have a few ice breakers, go over the basics of con rules, do's and don'ts, talk about what to expect, and how to have a blast!

sessions.title: Dealer's Den + Artist's Alley - Open to Public
Macro/Micro Meet
sessions.description:
This one is for the real Kaiju of Toronto! 
Stomp on over and indulge in photo ops and socialization with all of your resident size enthusiasts!

sessions.title: Meet the Guests of Honor
sessions.description: TBD

sessions.title: Fursuiter Sports Jersey Meet
sessions.description:
Fursuiters bring your Jerseys, equipment and other sportswear and come down and talk about sports, jersey design and collecting, and grab some photos!

Non fursuiters welcome!

sessions.title: Fursuit Dance Competition Preliminaries / PDC Auditions
sessions.description:
These are the closed door preliminaries for the Fursuit Dance Competition AND Pas Le Choix de Danser. If you are planning on dancing in either main event later on, you MUST attend this panel! No attendance outside of dancers/handlers is permitted.

A waiver form, along with parental consent for minors, will have been emailed to you, and need to filled out prior to the auditions. Please be sure to bring that with you to this panel.

sessions.title: So You Want To Run A Furry Event (Or You Don't, But You're Going To Anyway)
sessions.description: There's a joke that as you get older in the furry community, you end up on con staff or starting your own event. Now, you don't *have* to start your own event, but if you *want* to, we've assembled some experienced event runners and con staffers to talk you through it! Come learn from people who've done it, and ask some questions!

sessions.title: So you’re new to the fandom? Here’s what to expect.
sessions.description: Introduction to those new to the fandom but of course experienced fur’s more than welcome

sessions.title: VTubing and Content Creation
sessions.description: Want to be a VTuber or furry content creator? Join full-time VTuber - CorgiCam - for a deep-dive discussion on healthy stream practices, community-building, and social media management! Learn the ins-and-outs of streaming from a creator with over 10 years experience!

sessions.title: Magic: the Gathering - Bloomburrow Draft
sessions.description:
Location: Pier 4/5

Mice and rats, birds and bats. What Magic the Gathering set has ever been more perfect for our community than Bloomburrow? Draft the furry set and play against other furries.

sessions.title: Practical Furry Photography
sessions.description:
Love photographing fursuits? Just got your new camera and not sure how to use it? Or want to get the most out of your smartphone camera?

Tips on photographing fursuiters, getting better pictures, and overcoming the unique challenges of taking photos at a convention—that anyone can use! 

Bring your smartphones, DSLR / mirrorless and compact cameras! You can also try a DSLR or mirrorless camera if you don't have one. 

We'll end the presentation with a Q&A, and if there are any fursuiter or non-suiter who volunteer as subjects we'll also have some hands-on practice!

sessions.title: Kandi Trading
sessions.description: Meet up and trade Kandi friendship bracelets. Materials will not be provided, but feel free to bring your own bracelet making supplies.

sessions.title: Trash Animals Meet and Greet
sessions.description: Meetup for all kinds of trash animals! Raccoons, bears, squirrels, and pretty much any other fursonas that love garbage are welcome to come socialize.

sessions.title: Being a Minor in the fandom
sessions.description: Are you a young person or minor looking to find your place in the fandom at a young age? Maybe a parent or guardian trying to figure this weird "furry" thing out? If this is true, come by! This is perfect for you! We'll be discussing ways to find your community, how to make friends, and most importantly how to stay safe at a vulnerable age. I will also be taking questions and giving personalized advice

sessions.title: Monster Hunter: The Boardgame
sessions.description: Come take down big monsters in the board game based on the popular video game series. Up to 4 hunters, first come first served.

sessions.title: Fashion furries
sessions.description: Learn the basics to becoming a more stylish you, How to stay hot/cool with clothing and so much more!

sessions.title: Dealer's Den + Artist's Alley - Open to Public
Fursuit Masquerade Rehearsals
sessions.description: TBD

sessions.title: Cinna Skunk in Concert
sessions.description: Cinna Skunk is here to bring Appalachian Folk Music to Furnal Equinox. A mix of storytelling, ukulele folk music and lyrics about the mountain range he calls home.

sessions.title: Railfurs United
sessions.description: Just a gathering of railfurs, time to talk about everything regarding trains!

sessions.title: Dragon Tails and Scales of Ontario
sessions.description: Are you a Dragon, a Kobold or even a lizard etc. Then come on down to dragon tails and scales of Ontario where you can meet and greet fellow reptilian brothers and sisters and share interests like what inspired your scale-sona and what media dragons/scalies are featured in and the like of that nature. So if you're a scalie of any kind Alligator, crocodile, salamander etc or maybe you like scalies in general and aren't a scalie yourself. Then if that's the case come on down to Dragon Tails and Scales

sessions.title: Therianonthropy 101
sessions.description: A panel in which those who wish to learn the more hidden side of the furry world as a Therian and understand what it is or how it affects us day to day.

sessions.title: Let's get Blending
sessions.description: A chit chat session where you can ask questions about the digital creation process using blender and other tools, while I talk about the process and tools I use. This is a great place to learn some things if you're interested in getting into 3D creations.

sessions.title: Final Fantasy XIV meet and greet
sessions.description: A gathering for players of the popular MMORPG Final Fantasy XIV. Meet your fellow Warriors of Light and bond over your favourite parts of the game!

sessions.title: Atypical Winged-Thing Meetup
sessions.description: Do you have wings? Does your species normally not have wings? If so, come on down!

sessions.title: Change The Game - An Improvised Game Show
sessions.description: Inspired by Dropout's Game Changer, contestants play a game show where they don't know the game, the rules, or how to win. They have to play along and find out how to win before the other contestants!

sessions.title: DIY Furry Accessories
sessions.description: Accessories for all furries, it's easy! Want to learn how to make a hat for your fursuit? Or what everyday objects can be used as fun accessories? Learn how with Zaya, the crafter extraordinaire!

sessions.title: Cutthroat Artist
sessions.description: Four talented artists go head to head in a series of surprise, timed art challenges. Each round, our judge eliminates one artist until the winner is crowned! The twist? Each round, sabotages can be bid on by the artists and they can be inflicted on their competition. Join us and you may receive free art from our contestants!

sessions.title: A Queerer Furry History
sessions.description: You are already aware of the history of the furry fandom, but when, how and why did furries get to be SO QUEER? In this talk, Arrkay from the award winning video series "Culturally F'd" takes a second look into the queer origins of the furry fandom. Our journey takes us through homophobia fueled flame wars, a convention described as a "pride parade on acid", all the way to litterboxes in classrooms. Together we'll peer into the past of queer and trans furry artists, marches, frolics and raves, and even some pre-fandom stuff just for fun.

sessions.title: Prehistoric Furries Meet & Greet
sessions.description: Welcoming all Dinosaurs and other furries of species long forgotten. Meet your fellow furs from antiquity, and we'll party like it's the Mesozoic!

sessions.title: PCD
sessions.description:
Finally, some PCD you WANT to catch! Furnal's signature dance battle event similar to Floor Wars, Pas le Choix de Danser (English: "No Choice but to Dance") returns for its second year with MCs Avalanche and Gnaw, and DJ'd by Dodge Horse!  
 
Check out the exciting 1 on 1 dance battle action to see who will be crowned PCD 2025's champion!

sessions.title: Littlest Pet Shop and other figurines
sessions.description: Celebrating the history of the iconic big-eyed toy figurines and the fans who love them! Optional swap at the end.

sessions.title: Retro Game Roulette
sessions.description: Pressing the random game button on an emulator and seeing what cringe games we can try together

sessions.title: Furry Improv
sessions.description:
It's a bunch of furry animals making stuff up on the fly!
*Change*
It's a quick-thinking quick-speaking audience participation show!
*Change*
It's a bunch of games that make you think on your feet in front of an audience!
*Change*
It's Improv with Dralen, Hiker, and Leo! Come "Yes, and:" with us!

sessions.title: Stellar Harvey's Furry Feud!
sessions.description:
Just like family feud, but Furry!
Come on out and experience a game show that's sure to bring some laughs and memorable moments to your day!

sessions.title: Y Ddraig Goch, and other monsters in Welsh mythology
sessions.description: A look at mythical monsters present in Welsh mythology, with some storytelling and cultural insight thrown in for good measure.

sessions.title: 3DS StreetPass Meetup
sessions.description: Bring your 3DS, meet other Nintendo furs, get StreetPasses, and play some games!

sessions.title: Anyare's Art Jam [18+]
sessions.description:
Bring your sketchpad, tablet, supplies and creativity! Come hang out and draw with Anyare and Larkstarr! This is an interactive panel where we use word prompts to draw along with the artist! At the end of the prompts, we will all share our drawings. 
Post panel, Anyare will take photos of all the drawings (with permission!) and create an album of all the cool, creative and diverse artwork that was made.

While we draw, feel free to ask questions, learn some tips and tricks, talk about art styles and ask for feedback from others on your art. All skill level is welcome! Guests are also welcome to just come watch.

Please note, this is an 18+ Panel

sessions.title: Official V-Pets Furries Meetup
sessions.description: Do you collect virtual pets? Are you a fan of Tamagotchi, Digimon, GigaPets, etc.? Join our panel and meet other furries who love to collect ViPets! Don't forget to bring your own V-Pet to connect with others!

sessions.title: Dysgu Gyda'n Gilydd: Let's Learn Welsh Together!
sessions.description: Siwmae! If you know what that means, then this meet-up is for you! Whether you're just getting started, a fluent speaker, or still trying to work out when a C becomes a G, an CH, or an NGH, you'll be more that welcome at this meet to learn, practice, and enjoy Welsh.

sessions.title: Sea Shanty singalong
sessions.description:
Sing songs of the sea! Yes, you!
No experience required, no talent necessary, and the lyrics are up on screen if you want them. Come enjoy the music and join in!

sessions.title: ZOOLOGY 101 [18+]
sessions.description: A semester-length zoology class condensed into a single panel time slot. Featuring ridiculous audience polls, weird hands-on experiments, and strange drawing challenges - all taught by real, actual scientists. ZOOLOGY 101 is the only class where attendance is 99% of your grade.

sessions.title: Macchiato Stares At You
sessions.description: Want to be stared at by a weird looking ferret? This is the panel for that. Come get started at.

sessions.title: Babyfur & Ageplayer Meet 'n Greet [18+]
sessions.description: Babyfurs, lil’furs, caregivers and their bigger friends alike are invited to get together for some friendly cub chatter!  Bring your plushies and come reconnect with your friends, meet new ones and enjoy some colouring and other cub-friendly activities!

sessions.title: Friday Night Dance w/ DJ_Huwls
sessions.description: Join DJ_Huwls for their Hard Techno Set!

sessions.title: Werewolves: Eat your friends!
sessions.description: The classic hidden role social game, Werewolves, is here at Furnal Equinox! A village is trying to rid itself of werewolves before it's too late! New and veteran players welcome! It's a great way to meet new people and have fun!

sessions.title: Puppy play? What’s that? [18+]
sessions.description:
As the title holder of pup Canada 2024, I would like to give a small course on the different aspect of puppy play (social, bdsm, sexual, therapeutic) and give people a lists of the basic equipment you must have to begin playing on all fours safely (such a knee pads, protective glove, etc). 

I would like to be there to answer questions, showcase available puppy play gear (nothing sexual, just gear related to the puppy) and try to interest people in the community since it is a misconception that the community is only sexual. The fandom has changed a lot in the past year and the amount of « social pups » have increased a lot and the social/therapeutic benefits of it could help a lot of people in my opinion! 

Of course, since the main part of the community is based around bdsm, it would be an 18+ panel.

sessions.title: Friday Night Dance w/ Dodge vs. Claire
sessions.description: Join Dodge & Claire for their Bass House / Techno set!

sessions.title: Shibari 101: Tying the Knot [18+]
sessions.description:
Learn rope safety and basic ties.

This is for beginners who are interested in beginning their trek in the art of shibari.

sessions.title: Simply Monstrous Convention Horror Stories [18+]
sessions.description: Join Conreeaght and other Convention running guests with many years of volunteering, staffing, and even leadership experience as they regale with stories of colossal "challenges" and gigantic "near misses" and possibly even terror writ large from events gone by. Even though they can be monstrous - one rule remains. No names. Donations to the convention charity appreciated and any funds raised through our horrors help immensely.

sessions.title: Friday Night Dance w/ V FOR VIENNA
sessions.description: Join V FOR VIENNA for their Bass House / Festival Trap set!

sessions.title: Simply Monstrous Convention Horror Stories [18+]
sessions.description:
This is a Continuation of the panel Simply Monstrous Convention Horror Stories

Join Conreeaght and other Convention running guests with many years of volunteering, staffing, and even leadership experience as they regale with stories of colossal "challenges" and gigantic "near misses" and possibly even terror writ large from events gone by. Even though they can be monstrous - one rule remains. No names. Donations to the convention charity appreciated and any funds raised through our horrors help immensely.

sessions.description:
This is a continuation of the panel Shibari 101: Tying the Knot 

Learn rope safety and basic ties.

This is for beginners who are interested in beginning their trek in the art of shibari.

sessions.title: Werewolves: Eat your friends!
sessions.description:
This is a continuation of the game session for Werewolves: Eat your friends!

The classic hidden role social game, Werewolves, is here at Furnal Equinox! A village is trying to rid itself of werewolves before it's too late! New and veteran players welcome! It's a great way to meet new people and have fun!

sessions.title: Friday Night Dance w/ Physwolf
sessions.description: Join Physwolf for their Mainstage Set!

sessions.title: Fursuit Games
sessions.description: TBD

sessions.title: Animal Crossing: New Horizons - Switch Social Open Game
Kemono meet and greet
sessions.description: Are you a fan of kemono art and fursuits? Then this event might be for you! Hang out, chat, take some photos, and meet your fellow fans of all things kemono!

sessions.title: Pokémon Go Meetup!
sessions.description: Trainers!  Come gather to meet fellow trainers from across the globe to share friend codes, conduct some trades, and share knowledge with other players!  Whether you're a beginner or expert, come join us for some fun!

sessions.title: Pokemon Trading Card Game - Open Gaming
4-2-Floor: Fursuit Dancing Basics
sessions.description: If you're aiming for competitions, heading to a rave, or just having fun, learn how to dance in your fursuit while staying safe and improving your moves! Led by a FE dance comp veteran with over 10 years of experience, this workshop is open to all who want to get their tails shaking!

sessions.title: You, Me & DND
sessions.description:
A single character crowd interactive one shot D&D adventure.
Year 3 - Hosted by Nexus & Bootz

sessions.title: Stop the Bleed
sessions.description: Major injury can happen. Things can go wrong while driving, being attacked by an animal or by monsters invading Toronto. The Stop the Bleed course is a hands on course where students will learn and practice various techniques and equipment to stop bleeding. Bleeding, left uncontrolled is the #1 preventable cause of death after injury.

sessions.title: Rules for Writing Good Furry Fiction
sessions.description: A professional level presentation that enumerates the rules and guidelines that separate great stories from bad ones, with an eye towards the additional rules that apply to furry fiction specifically.

sessions.title: Vulpine Meet and Greet
sessions.description: Come meet other foxy friends!

sessions.title: Meet up for <18 Therian and Fursuiter (Parents Welcome)
sessions.description: Bring your parents with you to speak with other parents of the younger convention goers.  Young fursuiters can meet each other and make friends to spend the convention day with.  Parents can meet with other parents and ask questions.

sessions.title: Battle of Maple and Gravy
sessions.description: A dance battle panel workshop mostly for people curious to get into dancing and learn what it's like to participate in a battle!

sessions.title: Asexual Furs Meet and Greet
sessions.description: Do you identify as Asexual or are on the Asexual spectrum (Demisexual, Greysexual etc )? Are you one who is in a relationship with an Asexual identifying significant other? Are you uncertain if you are Asexual or fall under the spectrum? Or are you curious what exactly is Asexuality? Come meet others as we talk about the beauty of Asexuality! Allies are encouraged and welcome! (Garlic bread sadly not included)

sessions.title: Inflatable Monster Beasts
sessions.description: Yes, there are inflatable kaiju capable of devastating a major metropolitan area.  Play with oversized custom inflatables, chat with fellow enthusiasts, find out how to develop your own.  You can even bring your own inflatables (SFW only)!

sessions.title: Radio Operators United!
sessions.description: There are many types of radio operators, so come one and come all to a meetup about amateur (HAM) radio and other types of radios!

sessions.title: Pokemon TCG Pocket Tournament
sessions.description: A small tournament for the new Pokemon Pocket game!

sessions.title: All Abord the Rail-Away Express
sessions.description: Is it the destination or the journey that's more important? On the Rail-Away, the industrial crew have decided to offer both! Join the crew for this D&D one shot from The Seeker's Guide to Twisted Taverns!

sessions.title: Tour De Fur Fursuit Walk
sessions.description: Let's go stomping around downtown!  Explore Toronto's scenic waterfront, interact with the public and find some unique photo opportunities just outside the con hotel!

sessions.title: Colouring Collab: Monsters in Toronto
sessions.description: Love colouring sheets for a good cause? Participants will each receive a colouring sheet to complete. At the end of the session, everyone's sheets will be combined like a jigsaw puzzle to form a larger "Monsters in Toronto" themed drawing, which will be donated to the FE charity auction. Colouring sheets and materials provided.

sessions.title: So you want to go independent full time? The things you need to know before you jump in!
sessions.description: I'll be speaking about my experience as an independent creator and what it takes to do this full time!

sessions.title: Mario kart 8 Deluxe - Switch Social Open Game
Techniques for Writing Good Furry Fiction
sessions.description: A professional level presentation on the ways to get from zero to a published story that you're proud of and your audience loves.

sessions.title: Dealer's Den + Artist's Alley - Open to Public
Airplanes, Spacecraft and more
sessions.description: Just a gathering of av-geeks to talk about airplanes, and ADS-B and tracking airplanes as a hobby!

sessions.title: The Bird Meet
sessions.description:
Where birds come to meet~
And any others who like birds :>

sessions.title: TFTuesday Podcast - Live!
sessions.description: Come on down to a live recording of the TFTuesday podcast! This podcast focuses on the concept of transformation, mainly in the niche of the furry community, and what the theme of transformation and interest in it means as it relates to its fans. Our live recording will delve into a few specific topics before taking some audience Q&As!

sessions.title: Furries at my University???
sessions.description: Have you ever wondered if there are other furs hiding among you at your post-secondary institution? Do you want to start a furry club? We're here to show you just how you can do that- and the benefits between being unofficial vs an officially recognized club.

sessions.title: The Golden Age of Furry Small Press
sessions.description: Ever been curious how artists found each other as furry fandom developed in the '90s? Online image boards were not yet possible, so enter the small press - fanzines and mini-comics available by mail! Come see a (very personal) history of the furry zine scene and a retrospective of the artists that cemented the fandom's growth!

sessions.title: Xephyr & Anubis LIVE
sessions.description: Xephyr is an independent Hard Rock band of Clumzy Lion, Cobalt and Turi The Dragon. The show opener will be Damiano's Elysium (featuring Anubis).

sessions.title: Pokemon Spelling Test
sessions.description: Have you been paying close attention to the names of the pokemon you've been catching?? Let's find out! Come take a fun test and see just how sharp your memory is! Pokemon in this test range from Kanto to Paldea! Test papers as well as pens and pencils will be provided!

sessions.title: Behind the Scenes: The Monsters of FE
sessions.description: Curious about what it entails to run FE? How does one get involved? Do you need a special skillset? Can you still enjoy the con as a staff member? Come learn about the volunteers, what's involved, and ask any questions you might have!

sessions.title: VRChat Meet-and-Greet
sessions.description:
Plug in! Log on! Let's get virtual in reality!

Join us for our annual VRChat meet-and-greet, in-person! Whether you're brand-new to the VR scene or a longtime "Trusted User," join us to link up with friends from across the digital divide and chat about all the amazing things you can do in VRChat. Learn about everything from raves to games to chillout worlds to even building your own avatar and world. Experience all of the fun virtual groups of friends and furs you can meet along the way right here in reality.

We are VR!

sessions.title: King of Tokyo / New York - Open Gaming
Build a Bear Meetup
sessions.description: Bring your bear (and other) furry friends to meet other plushie collectors. If you have clothing, bring that too!!

sessions.title: Furry Worldbuilding!
sessions.description: Have you ever wanted to build a world for yourself, a universe for your characters to exist in, a setting to tell your tales, or simply having fun building fictional universes? Then this is the panel for you! We’ll be going over some general rules of worldbuilding, add in some anthropomorphic animals, and troubleshoot your worlds and stories. Bring your creativity, bring your characters, bring your stories, and let’s have some fun!

sessions.title: Mario Party Tournament
sessions.description: Do you like Mario Party? Collecting Coins? Collecting Stars? Join us for the recent edition Mario Party Jamboree and battle in our

sessions.title: Teaselbone's Art and Freelance Corner
sessions.description: Showing how I do some of my art while also discussing freelance ideas and practices within the furry fandom.

sessions.title: Ride the Rocket: A Guide to Public Transit
sessions.description:
Ever wanted to ride the bus but weren't sure how? Take the train in a new city but felt intimidated? Or just better understand how to utilize public transit? Demystify the world of busses, trains, and everything in between! Come learn the ways of the fare card, how to transit-orient your life, feel confident making that transfer, and see how it can all tie into your local furry community.

After the panel, put your newfound knowledge to work by joining for a ride on the TTC! You'll experience Toronto's streetcars and subways and be welcome to snap some fursuit photos along the journey. Ride time approx. ~1 hour

sessions.title: Furries and Alternative Fashion
sessions.description: What do furries and lolitas have in common? A lot more than you think! Come learn how to wear your fursuit in the best in alternative fashion and street wear. Best place to shop online, how to adjust clothes for fursuiting, and more!

sessions.title: Fursuit Masquerade
sessions.description: TBD

sessions.title: Rodents!
sessions.description: Come all ye rodents and those in need of a good chew!  We'll gather to discuss the wonderful world of rodents of all shapes and sizes.  Be it in movies, books, games, pets, and the fandom, we're here to share it all!  Fursuit photo at the end for all Rodent suiters!

sessions.title: Event Mastery: Where Venue Management Meets Late-Night Satire
sessions.description:
Ever wondered what goes on behind the scenes of hotel selection and venue management? Well, buckle up, because you're in for a wild ride! Join me as I take you on an exciting journey through the ins and outs of the entire process. From selecting the perfect venue to managing every little detail — this is your chance to dive deep into the world of event planning.

But wait, there’s more! This won’t just be a typical learning experience. Think late-night show meets masterclass, with a sprinkle of satire and some unexpected special guests popping in along the way. It's informative, it's fun, and it's guaranteed to keep you on your toes.

Come for the knowledge, stay for the laughs — and let’s make this a learning experience like no other!

sessions.title: Fishing 101
sessions.description: Learn the basics of fishing and how to catch the lake or river monster of your dreams! From regulations, to gearing up, and how to actually fish, we'll teach anyone who is interested in fishing where to start.

sessions.title: Culturally F'd 10 Year Anniversary Celebration
sessions.description: Culturally F'd! The Ursa Major Award winning video series celebrates 10 years of making videos by, about and for furries, exploring the many different forms of media that furries take part in and celebrate. Originally premiering at Furnal Equinox 2015, the channel has grown and evolved a lot with the times. Screening clips from our entire 10 year history including "Fursuit History" "The Bone Zone" "Puplift: A Dogs Guide to Space" and more!

sessions.title: Libertalia: Winds of Galecrest
sessions.description: In the world of Galecrest, sky pirates set sail on the winds in search of adventure, treasure, and glory. As an admiral, you command a vast and varied crew … but so do your rivals sailing other ships in the pirate fleet. Each day the fleet lands on a different island where you’ll send a crew member to collect your share of the loot, hoping they’ll return to boost your growing group of characters. A board game for up to six players, featuring 40 different anthro crew members.

sessions.title: Monster Jeopardy!
sessions.description: You're going to need some monster-sized brain power if you want to conquer this year's board of sixty-one answers and questions, not to mention your opponents also vying for control!  Tap into your knowledge of high culture and pop culture in this classic trivia contest to stand above all others!  Once again returning will be our team play format where the three contestants who pass the pre-game trivia challenge will have to pick a partner from the audience, so either bring a trusted ally or be prepared to form an uneasy alliance!

sessions.title: Maid/Butler Raid!!
sessions.description: Do you have a MAID COSTUME or a BUTLER'S OUTFIT? Or a desire to CLEAN?? Show up in your best, 'cause we're meeting for a big maid group photo! Some discussion of cleaning products and solutions may occur.

sessions.title: Rock Band Jam Session
sessions.description: Calling all Rock Band/Guitar Hero enthusiasts! Jam and sing your hearts out together as we jam through many songs to jam to throughout the Rock Band/Guitar Hero games series'.

sessions.title: The Vore Panel [18+]
sessions.description: What is vore? Why do people enjoy being swallowed alive? More importantly, why is it in every cartoon and piece of media? Come learn and laugh with this comedic and informative presentation hosted by Marshmallow, with games, vore furs, and more!

sessions.title: The Dragstravaganza! Hosted by Alissa Brink & Bear Sailor Moon [18+]
sessions.description:
"We are BACK BACK BACK BACK BACK AGAIN! The Dragstravaganza with Alissa Brink & Bear SailorMoon! Come join us for an evening of incredible drag. Whether its your first time ever seeing a drag show or you've lost track of how many drag bars you've been in ALL ARE WELCOME!
Get ready to Cheer, Gasp, Laugh and Scream!"

Chevron is a gray wolf, gamer, and event host from New Jersey. He works with several VRChat-based convention groups like the Furality Online Xperience, TailBass, Misho's Feeshquarium, Lords of Floof, WaterWolf, Projekt Community, and xCirrex Media to create events and bring people together for fun nights, games, friendship, and great times. He hosts Thursday VRChat Games alongside NoxTheSergal every week (which are often attended with full instances), as well as in-person gatherings monthly. He passionately embraces VRChat and its rave and convention scene, especially with Furnal Equinox, CozyCon, Projekt Community, WaterWolf, and the Furality Online Xperience. You'll find him most often sharing photos on his art galleries to help promote his favorite events and organizations. Furrydelphia, Furnal Equinox, and Anthro New England's first ever VRChat Meet-and-Greets and Intro Panels were co-hosted by TJCoyote, Chief, Chevron, Lilithe Lotor, mBlade, and members of the Fluffy Fur Friends. Motivated by the TailBass and Furality VRChat portals, Chevron is now working to set up VRChat portals and meets at other in-person conventions.

He serves as a Photographer for the Furality Online Xperience, operator for the Operations Department for WaterWolf, Events Host for Projekt Community, and a tournament co-host for xCirrex Media events.

Chevron's love and passion for Furnal Equinox motivated him to cosplay as "Badgie" (Virtual Furnal Equinox 2021's unofficial mascot made of nothing but attendee badges) at the in-person convention in 2022. He reprized his role in-person in 2023 and 2024, and also attends other conventions as "Badgie" who is often referred to as "Attendee Man."

Chevron first attended Furnal Equinox in March 2021 over VRChat. The experience was so enjoyable that he dared to compared his experience at Furnal Equinox to Furality 2000 (November 2020). This motivated him to attend the in-person Furnal Equinox convention for the first time in March 2022. The trip was a first of many for Chevron: His first time in Canada, first time using Lyft, and first time public suiting and marching in a fursuit parade. Chevron has now added Furnal Equinox to his list of yearly attended conventions.

A lifelong player of EVE Online, Mechwarrior, Armed Assault III, Halo, Command & Conquer, and Dance Dance Revolution, Chevron holds a particular appreciation for older games of the late 1990s-early 2000s, such as the first Ghost Recon (2002) and Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time. His first video game was Mario on the original Game Boy when he was five years old. His admiration of cyberpunk and all things futuristic is on full display with his Illumi Cyberwear LED visor. His fursuit was made by Sarahcat. Outside of the fandom, he works in the IT industry as a cybersecurity administrator and is (jokingly) addicted to Mountain Dew.

Chevron's ultimate goal is to bring people together for fun and great times. He embraces the future with open arms and is eager to dive right into all the fun that can be had together with friends and the fandom.

speakers.bio:
My name is Daniel Walsh, but other furries call me Taque! I discovered the furry community when I was in air cadets back in 2015 and was an active member of the Newfoundland Furry and Anthro Society during grade school.

I recently moved to Montreal for work and was looking to get involved with local furry groups, that is when I attended my first furry convention Canfurence 2022. I was very anxious about attending as I didn’t know anyone at the convention and was overwhelmed when exploring the venue. The attendees of the furry convention were very friendly and showed me how to enjoy the convention to the fullest! Since then I’ve been hooked on attending furry conventions and meeting new and experienced furs along the way!

I have been grateful that the furry community is full of accepting and friendly people. I would like to share my experiences to help new attendees enjoy furry conventions, just like how other experienced attendees helped me!

You can follow Darby @darbington on FA or Instagram!
